Name: popuseacl
Type: SWITCH
Default-Value: 0
Last-Modified: 2.3.17

Enforce IMAP ACLs in the pop server.  Due to the nature of the POP3
protocol, the only rights which are used by the pop server are 'r', 't',
and 's' for the owner of the mailbox.  The 'r' right allows the user to
open the mailbox and list/retrieve messages.  The 't' right allows the user
to delete messages.  The 's' right allows messages retrieved by the user to
have the \\Seen flag set (only if *popuseimapflags* is also enabled).
